(2, 1, '2011-09-19 13:17:01', '2011-09-19 13:17:01', 'If you are a new resident of St. Regis Park or a longer term resident, welcome to our web page. We believe our City is a wonderful place to live. The City of St. Regis Park was first incorporated in 1953. It is a 4th Class City with over 600 homes. As a 4th Class City, St. Regis Park has control over development and zoning , the ability to raise revenue thru taxation, and possesses police powers.\r\n\r\nHere you will find news about the City, basic information on a wide variety of topics and ways in which you can contact City officials with any comments, questions or problems you may have. Most important of all, this City web site, like the City’s government itself, is for <em>you!</em> Let us know how we can help you in any way.', 'Welcome', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sample-page', '', '', '2011-10-12 02:07:42', '2011-10-12 02:07:42', '', 0, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?page_id=2', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(4, 1, '2011-09-19 13:17:01', '2011-09-19 13:17:01', 'This is an example page. It''s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I''m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin'' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://www.stregispark.net/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!', 'Sample Page', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision', '', '', '2011-09-19 13:17:01', '2011-09-19 13:17:01', '', 2, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?p=4', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(6, 1, '2011-09-19 20:19:19', '2011-09-19 20:19:19', 'Click the links below for PDF version of ordinances.\r\n<a href=''http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/COVER-SHEET.pdf''>COVER SHEET</a>\r\n<a href=''http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/TABLE-OF-CONTENTS.pdf''>TABLE OF CONTENTS</a>\r\n<a href=''http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/TITLE-I-GENERAL-PROVISIONS.pdf''>TITLE I  GENERAL PROVISIONS</a>\r\n<a href=''http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/TITLE-III-ADMINISTRATION.pdf''>TITLE III  ADMINISTRATION</a>\r\n<a href=''http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/TITLE-IX-GENERAL-REGULATIONS.pdf''>TITLE IX  GENERAL REGULATIONS</a>\r\n<a href=''http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/TITLE-V-PUBLIC-WORKS.pdf''>TITLE V  PUBLIC WORKS</a>\r\n<a href=''http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/TITLE-VII-TRAFFIC-CODE.pdf''>TITLE VII  TRAFFIC CODE</a>\r\n<a href=''http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/TITLE-XI-BUSINESS-REGULATIONS.pdf''>TITLE XI  BUSINESS REGULATIONS</a>\r\n<a href=''http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/TITLE-XIII-GENERAL-OFFENSES.pdf''>TITLE XIII  GENERAL OFFENSES</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Most Commonly Used Ordinances</strong> / <a href="http://www.stregispark.net/cityordinances/ordinances.html" title="All Ordinances">All Ordinances</a>\r\n\r\nThe following are excerpts from the ordinances adopted for the City of St. Regis Park. The numbers refer to the full ordinance contained in the complete listing. For additional information, refer to the number of the complete listing of ordinances.\r\n\r\n<strong>ANIMALS</strong>\r\n90.02 No owner shall permit an animal to run at large. The owner is liable for all damage caused by the animal.\r\n90.06 Pooper-scooper The owner is responsible for picking up and disposing of his/her animal''s waste outside of his/her property. There is a penalty of $5.00 to $25 per violation. (90.99)\r\n\r\n<strong>BUILDING REGULATIONS AND PERMITS</strong>\r\n<strong>150.16</strong> <em>A)</em> Building permits from the city are required for any building or structure, including fences, pools, and auxiliary building. Contact the Mayor or designated city councilman or councilwoman.\r\n<strong>150.16</strong> Property maintenance. All property owners must maintain lots and structures erected thereon in reasonable condition and appearance.\r\n<strong>150.17</strong> Construction materials are specified.\r\n<strong>150.18</strong> Garages, porches and driveways\r\n<strong>150.19</strong> Fences and porches\r\n<em>A)</em> No fence may extend beyond the front wall of the house.\r\n<em>E)</em> A fence must be made of ornamental metal, wire, or wood and shall not be over 6 feet in height.\r\n<strong>150.20</strong> Swimming pools\r\n<strong>150.22</strong> auxiliary structures, such as utility sheds, playhouses\r\n<strong>150.23</strong> corner sight triangles Plants in the triangles at the intersections shall be less that 2 feet high or trees shall be clear of branches from 2 feet to 6 feet above the ground.\r\n<strong>150.27</strong> Fees for permits\r\n\r\n<strong>GARBAGE</strong>\r\n<strong>50.01</strong> <em>A)</em> No garbage, grass or trash shall be placed at the curbsides before 3:00 p.m. the day prior to the pickup.\r\n<em>B)</em> All garbage cans and items not collected shall be removed from the curbside by 7:00 p.m. the day of the pickup.\r\n\r\n<strong>NUISANCES</strong>\r\n<strong>92.01</strong> Nuisances defined\r\n<strong>92.03</strong> These particular nuisances are unlawful:\r\n<em>A)</em> dangerous trees or other materials close to the street\r\n<em>B)</em> an accumulation of rubbish on the property\r\n<em>C)</em> the storage of explosive materials which create a safety hazard\r\n<em>D)</em> weeds and grass over 9 inches in height\r\n<em>H)</em> junk, scrap metal, inoperable vehicles, automobile parts\r\n\r\n<strong>PARKING</strong>\r\n<strong>70.02</strong> Cars must park on the right-hand side of the road, parallel to the curb. No parking is permitted at the curbs painted yellow or in front of any public or private driveway.\r\n<strong>70.03</strong> limitations of parking. No boats, boat trailers, recreational vehicles, motor homes, bus, tractor, trailer, or camper shall be parked or stored in a front, side, or street side yard, or on the street.\r\n<strong>70.06</strong> No vehicle shall remain parked on the street for 24 consecutive hours, subject to a fine between $20 and $100 (70.99)\r\n<strong>70.13</strong> J) No commercial or similar vehicle, school bus, or farm or construction equipment shall be parked or displayed in the side or front area of any residence.\r\n\r\n<strong>SIDEWALKS</strong>\r\n<strong>91.30 - 91.34</strong> Homeowners are to keep the sidewalks free from obstruction, including ice and snow.', 'Ordinances', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ordinances', '', '', '2012-08-29 17:13:13', '2012-08-29 17:13:13', '', 0, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?page_id=6', 0, 'page', '', 0),
