ved from the curbside by 7:00 p.m. the day of the pickup.\r\n\r\n<strong>NUISANCES</strong>\r\n92.01 Nuisances defined\r\n92.03 These particular nuisances are unlawful:\r\nA) dangerous trees or other materials close to the street\r\nB) an accumulation of rubbish on the property\r\nC) the storage of explosive materials which create a safety hazard\r\nD) weeds and grass over 9 inches in height\r\nH) junk, scrap metal, inoperable vehicles, automobile parts\r\n\r\n<strong>PARKING</strong>\r\n70.02 Cars must park on the right-hand side of the road, parallel to the curb. No parking is permitted at the curbs painted yellow or in front of any public or private driveway.\r\n70.03 limitations of parking. No boats, boat trailers, recreational vehicles, motor homes, bus, tractor, trailer, or camper shall be parked or stored in a front, side, or street side yard, or on the street.\r\n70.06 No vehicle shall remain parked on the street for 24 consecutive hours, subject to a fine between $20 and $100 (70.99)\r\n70.13 J) No commercial or similar vehicle, school bus, or farm or construction equipment shall be parked or displayed in the side or front area of any residence.\r\n\r\n<strong>SIDEWALKS</strong>\r\n91.30 - 91.34 Homeowners are to keep the sidewalks free from obstruction, including ice and snow.', 'Ordinances', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-revision-6', '', '', '2011-09-26 15:33:44', '2011-09-26 15:33:44', '', 6, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?p=32', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(38, 1, '2011-09-20 14:39:51', '2011-09-20 14:39:51', 'The City of St. Regis Park has a Mayor/Council form of government. The Mayor is elected by popular vote and serves a term of four (4) years. There are seven (7) council members, who are elected by popular vote and serve a term of two (2) years.\r\n\r\nBrandt Davis is the Mayor. He can be reached by calling or you can <a href="mailto:stregispark@aol.com">email him by clicking here</a>.\r\n\r\nBeginning with the new terms of office in January 2007 the Mayor is paid $500.00 per month and Council members are paid $100.00 per month.\r\n\r\nThe City also has two appointed officers:\r\n<table width="300px" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Treasurer</strong></td>\r\n<td>Talbott Allen</td>\r\n<td>451-3776</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Citation Officer</strong></td>\r\n<td>Drew Amon</td>\r\n<td>451-6360</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nThe positions of mayor and city council are obtained by filing for non-partisan elections held the first Tuesday of November. To run for Mayor or a council position a person must file with the Board of Elections prior to August 12 in order to be placed on the ballot in November. For more information contact the Board of Elections at 574-6100.\r\n\r\nThe City Council meets on the 1st Tuesday of every month at 7:30 p.m.. The meetings are held at the McMahan Fire District, 4318 Taylorsville Road. Notices of the meetings are published in the monthly newsletter. The meetings are open to the public and your comments are welcome during Citizen Participation at the beginning of every City Council meeting.', 'Council', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '10-revision-6', '', '', '2011-09-20 14:39:51', '2011-09-20 14:39:51', '', 10, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?p=38', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
