 the 1st Tuesday of every month at 7:30 p.m.. The meetings are held at the McMahan Fire District, 4318 Taylorsville Road. Notices of the meetings are published in the monthly newsletter. The meetings are open to the public and your comments are welcome during Citizen Participation at the beginning of every City Council meeting.', 'Council', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '10-revision-14', '', '', '2011-09-26 23:51:02', '2011-09-26 23:51:02', '', 10, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?p=46', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(47, 1, '2011-09-27 19:40:39', '2011-09-27 19:40:39', 'The City of St. Regis Park has a contract with Rumpke of Kentucky to provide for trash collection and recycling. Trash is collected weekly on Tuesdays. The contract calls for rear door pickup of three cans of trash. However, trash containers may be left at the curb for pickup. Trash is picked up as scheduled unless those days fall on Christmas or New Years. Trash pickup is not made on those holidays, but are made on the following day.\r\n\r\nYard waste will be collected curbside on Tuesdays from March through December. Yard waste collection during the Winter months will be on an on-call basis. Special arrangement can be made for extra pickups. Please call Rumpke directly to arrange these pickups. If you experience any problems with trash pickup please call Rumpke directly at 568-3800 or contact the City Council person overseeing City Services to resolve the problem. Please do not put out trash containers until late in the evening before pickup days and take your cans back to the house as soon after pickup as possible.\r\n\r\n<strong>NOTE:</strong> Should Memorial Day, July 4, Labor Day, Thanksgiving, Christmas or New Year’s Day fall in a given week, collections following the holiday are moved back one day.\r\n\r\n<strong>YARD WASTE</strong> pick up will start the first Tuesday of March.\r\n\r\n<strong>YARD WASTE</strong> pick up ends the last Tuesday of December.\r\n\r\n<strong>CHRISTMAS TREE </strong>removal will take place on the second Tuesday in January.', 'Trash Collection', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'trash-collection', '', '', '2012-07-12 17:38:23', '2012-07-12 17:38:23', '', 0, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?page_id=47', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(48, 1, '2011-09-27 19:40:07', '2011-09-27 19:40:07', 'The City of St. Regis Park has a contract with Rumpke of Kentucky to provide for trash collection and recycling. Trash is collected twice weekly on Tuesdays and Fridays. The contract calls for rear door pickup of two cans of trash. However, trash containers may be left at the curb for pickup. Trash is picked up as scheduled unless those days fall on Christmas or New Years. Trash pickup is not made on those holidays, but are made on the following day.\n\nYard waste will be collected curbside on Tuesdays from March through December. Yard waste collection during the Winter months will be on an on-call basis. Special arrangement can be made for extra pickups. Please call Rumpke directly to arrange these pickups. If you experience any problems with trash pickup please call Rumpke directly at 568-3800 or contact the City Council person overseeing City Services to resolve the problem. Please do not put out trash containers until late in the evening before pickup days and take your cans back to the house as soon after pickup as possible.\n\n<strong>NOTE:</strong> Should Memorial Day, July 4, Labor Day, Thanksgiving, Christmas or New Year’s Day fall in a given week, collections following the holiday are moved back one day.\n \n<strong>YARD WASTE</strong> pick up will start the first Tuesday of March.\n\n<strong>YARD WASTE</strong> pick up ends the last Tuesday of December.\n<strong>CHRISTMAS TREE </strong>removal will take place on the second Tuesday in January.\n', 'Trash Collection', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '47-revision', '', '', '2011-09-27 19:40:07', '2011-09-27 19:40:07', '', 47, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?p=48', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(50, 1, '2011-09-27 19:42:23', '2011-09-27 19:42:23', '<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-141" title="propertytaxes" src="http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/propertytaxes.gif" alt="" width="190" height="100" /><strong>Send tax payments to:</strong>\r\nCity of St. Regis Park\r\nc/o River City Bank\r\n2501 Bardstown Road\r\nLouisville, KY 40205\r\n\r\nThe City''s activities are funded largely by an annual property tax levy. The property taxes are levied on the real property values of each home as supplied by the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator (PVA). St. Regis Park property tax bills are  mailed out in July. The payments are due October 31st. Penalties and interest applies to late payments of the bill. Please check the property tax bill you receive for any penalties which may apply. Bills are not sent to mortgage companies by the City. It is the property owners responsibility to do this. Tax bills that remain unpaid on November 1 are delinquent. Liens are filed for tax bills that remain unpaid on January 1. The tax bill is generally paid out of an escrow account . Please check with your mortgage company if you have any question about a property tax escrow arrangement. Homestead or Disability exemptions are allowed residents of retirement age and those who are handicapped. If you believe you qualify for Homestead Exemption or Disability Exemption, please contact the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administration for details.\r\n\r\n<strong>MULTIPLE PAYMENT OF TAXES</strong>\r\nIf the City receives more than one payment of City taxes, the extra payment is remitted to the property owner – not the mortgage company. The City makes all multiple payment refunds after the payment deadline of October 31.\r\nThe Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator reassesses all real estate properties throughout Jefferson County approximately every two years.The City of St. Regis Park bases its property tax  on the Jefferson County property assessments. If you take exception to the assessed value of your property and want to appeal it, you must contact the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator. The telephone number for the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator is included with the list of telephone numbers contained in this brochure.', 'Taxes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'taxes', '', '', '2012-05-04 21:24:29', '2012-05-04 21:24:29', '', 0, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?page_id=50', 0, 'page', '', 0),
