(139, 1, '2011-09-28 15:39:07', '2011-09-28 15:39:07', '<strong>Most Commonly Used Ordinances</strong> / <a href="http://www.stregispark.net/ordinances/ordinances.html" title="All Ordinances">All Ordinances</a>\r\n\r\nThe following are excerpts from the ordinances adopted for the City of St. Regis Park. The numbers refer to the full ordinance contained in the complete listing. For additional information, refer to the number of the complete listing of ordinances.\r\n\r\n<strong>ANIMALS</strong>\r\n90.02 No owner shall permit an animal to run at large. The owner is liable for all damage caused by the animal.\r\n90.06 Pooper-scooper The owner is responsible for picking up and disposing of his/her animal''s waste outside of his/her property. There is a penalty of $5.00 to $25 per violation. (90.99)\r\n\r\n<strong>BUILDING REGULATIONS AND PERMITS</strong>\r\n150.16 A) Building permits from the city are required for any building or structure, including fences, pools, and auxiliary building. Contact the Mayor or designated city councilman or councilwoman.\r\n150.16 Property maintenance. All property owners must maintain lots and structures erected thereon in reasonable condition and appearance.\r\n150.17 Construction materials are specified.\r\n150.18 Garages, porches and driveways\r\n150.19 Fences and porches\r\nA) No fence may extend beyond the front wall of the house.\r\nE) A fence must be made of ornamental metal, wire, or wood and shall not be over 6 feet in height.\r\n150.20 Swimming pools\r\n150.22 auxiliary structures, such as utility sheds, playhouses\r\n150.23 corner sight triangles Plants in the triangles at the intersections shall be less that 2 feet high or trees shall be clear of branches from 2 feet to 6 feet above the ground.\r\n150.27 Fees for permits\r\n\r\n<strong>GARBAGE</strong>\r\n50.01 A) No garbage, grass or trash shall be placed at the curbsides before 3:00 p.m. the day prior to the pickup.\r\nB) All garbage cans and items not collected shall be removed from the curbside by 7:00 p.m. the day of the pickup.\r\n\r\n<strong>NUISANCES</strong>\r\n92.01 Nuisances defined\r\n92.03 These particular nuisances are unlawful:\r\nA) dangerous trees or other materials close to the street\r\nB) an accumulation of rubbish on the property\r\nC) the storage of explosive materials which create a safety hazard\r\nD) weeds and grass over 9 inches in height\r\nH) junk, scrap metal, inoperable vehicles, automobile parts\r\n\r\n<strong>PARKING</strong>\r\n70.02 Cars must park on the right-hand side of the road, parallel to the curb. No parking is permitted at the curbs painted yellow or in front of any public or private driveway.\r\n70.03 limitations of parking. No boats, boat trailers, recreational vehicles, motor homes, bus, tractor, trailer, or camper shall be parked or stored in a front, side, or street side yard, or on the street.\r\n70.06 No vehicle shall remain parked on the street for 24 consecutive hours, subject to a fine between $20 and $100 (70.99)\r\n70.13 J) No commercial or similar vehicle, school bus, or farm or construction equipment shall be parked or displayed in the side or front area of any residence.\r\n\r\n<strong>SIDEWALKS</strong>\r\n91.30 - 91.34 Homeowners are to keep the sidewalks free from obstruction, including ice and snow.', 'Ordinances', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-revision-8', '', '', '2011-09-28 15:39:07', '2011-09-28 15:39:07', '', 6, 'http://www.stregispark.net/index.php/2011/09/28/6-revision-8/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(140, 1, '2011-10-14 14:05:16', '2011-10-14 14:05:16', '<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-141" title="propertytaxes" src="http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/propertytaxes.gif" alt="" width="190" height="100" />Send tax payments to:<br /\nCity of St. Regis Park, 3917 Solutions Center, Chicago, IL 60677-3009\nThe City''s activities are funded largely by an annual property tax levy. The property taxes are levied on the real property values of each home as supplied by the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator (PVA). St. Regis Park property tax bills are  mailed out in July. The payments are due October 31st. Penalties and interest applies to late payments of the bill. Please check the property tax bill you receive for any penalties which may apply. Bills are not sent to mortgage companies by the City. It is the property owners responsibility to do this. Tax bills that remain unpaid on November 1 are delinquent. Liens are filed for tax bills that remain unpaid on January 1. The tax bill is generally paid out of an escrow account . Please check with your mortgage company if you have any question about a property tax escrow arrangement. Homestead or Disability exemptions are allowed residents of retirement age and those who are handicapped. If you believe you qualify for Homestead Exemption or Disability Exemption, please contact the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administration for details.\n\n<strong>MULTIPLE PAYMENT OF TAXES</strong>\nIf the City receives more than one payment of City taxes, the extra payment is remitted to the property owner – not the mortgage company. The City makes all multiple payment refunds after the payment deadline of October 31.\nThe Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator reassesses all real estate properties throughout Jefferson County approximately every two years.The City of St. Regis Park bases its property tax  on the Jefferson County property assessments. If you take exception to the assessed value of your property and want to appeal it, you must contact the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator. The telephone number for the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator is included with the list of telephone numbers contained in this brochure.', 'Taxes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '50-autosave', '', '', '2011-10-14 14:05:16', '2011-10-14 14:05:16', '', 50, 'http://www.stregispark.net/index.php/2011/10/13/50-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
