(151, 1, '2011-10-19 16:02:40', '2011-10-19 16:02:40', 'The City of St. Regis Park provides for the regular resurfacing and repair of the City streets. Please call the city office phone number if you observe a particular problem or pothole on a city street. The City is also responsible for traffic signs. When utilizing traffic or utility poles for “lost dog or cat”  or yard sale signs, we request that all such signs be removed within one week and without damage to the poles.\r\n\r\nLouisville Gas and Electric maintains all street lights within the City. If you notice a street light that is out or in need of repair please contact LG&E at the number listed in this brochure or call the city office.\r\nThe City provides for the salting and sanding and snow removal from streets based on established crtiteria set by the Mayor and the City Council. The service is provided by private contract to the City. If you experience a problem during the snow and ice season please call the City office or the City official overseeing City Services.', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '151', '', '', '2012-06-29 12:46:11', '2012-06-29 12:46:11', '', 0, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?p=151', 9, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(152, 1, '2011-10-19 16:02:40', '2011-10-19 16:02:40', 'The City of St. Regis Park has no jurisdiction over the drainage and sewer services provided within the City. Total responsibility for these services and problems is assumed by the Metropolitan Sewer District. These services are paid for by an addttion to your Louisville Water Company bill. The number for the Metropolitan Sewer District is contained in this brochure. If a problem continues to exist after initial contact with MSD, it may be possible for a City official to intercede on your behalf. Please try the Metropolitan Sewer District trouble line first.', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '152', '', '', '2012-06-29 12:46:11', '2012-06-29 12:46:11', '', 0, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?p=152', 8, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(153, 1, '2011-10-19 16:02:40', '2011-10-19 16:02:40', 'The City issues building permits and letters of compliance. When planning any building, addition to an existing structure, and fence, a resident should contact the City Council person overseeing Buildings and Improvements. Detail plans and specifications for all planned buildings and/or improvements should be submitted to this council member. When the plans and specifications have been approved, a building permit or letter of compliance will be issued. Building permits for fences, utility sheds, playhouses, and other auxiliary structure will be issued by the city.  Permits for houses, garages, and building additions will be issued by the Jefferson County Code Enforcement Division upon the presentation of a letter of compliance from the City of St. Regis Park.', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '153', '', '', '2012-06-29 12:46:11', '2012-06-29 12:46:11', '', 0, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?p=153', 5, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(154, 1, '2011-10-19 16:02:40', '2011-10-19 16:02:40', 'Send tax payments to:\r\nCity of St. Regis Park, 3917 Solutions Center, Chicago, IL 60677-3009\r\n\r\nThe City’s activities are funded largely by an annual property tax levy. The property taxes are levied on the real property values of each home as supplied by the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator (PVA). St. Regis Park property tax bills are  mailed out in July. The payments are due October 31st. Penalties and interest applies to late payments of the bill. Please check the property tax bill you receive for any penalties which may apply. Bills are not sent to mortgage companies by the City. It is the property owners responsibility to do this. Tax bills that remain unpaid on November 1 are delinquent. Liens are filed for tax bills that remain unpaid on January 1. The tax bill is generally paid out of an escrow account . Please check with your mortgage company if you have any question about a property tax escrow arrangement. Homestead or Disability exemptions are allowed residents of retirement age and those who are handicapped. If you believe you qualify for Homestead Exemption or Disability Exemption, please contact the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administration for details.\r\n\r\nMULTIPLE PAYMENT OF TAXES\r\nIf the City receives more than one payment of City taxes, the extra payment is remitted to the property owner – not the mortgage company. The City makes all multiple payment refunds after the payment deadline of October 31.\r\nThe Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator reassesses all real estate properties throughout Jefferson County approximately every two years.The City of St. Regis Park bases its property tax  on the Jefferson County property assessments. If you take exception to the assessed value of your property and want to appeal it, you must contact the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator. The telephone number for the Jefferson County Property Valuation Administrator is included with the list of telephone numbers contained in this brochure.', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '154', '', '', '2012-06-29 12:46:11', '2012-06-29 12:46:11', '', 0, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?p=154', 10, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(155, 1, '2011-10-19 16:02:40', '2011-10-19 16:02:40', 'The City of St. Regis Park has a contract with Rumpke of Kentucky to provide for trash collection and recycling. Trash is collected twice weekly on Tuesdays and Fridays. The contract calls for rear door pickup of two cans of trash. However, trash containers may be left at the curb for pickup. Trash is picked up as scheduled unless those days fall on Christmas or New Years. Trash pickup is not made on those holidays, but are made on the following day.\r\n\r\nYard waste will be collected curbside on Tuesdays from March through December. Yard waste collection during the Winter months will be on an on-call basis. Special arrangement can be made for extra pickups. Please call Rumpke directly to arrange these pickups. If you experience any problems with trash pickup please call Rumpke directly at 568-3800 or contact the City Council person overseeing City Services to resolve the problem. Please do not put out trash containers until late in the evening before pickup days and take your cans back to the house as soon after pickup as possible.\r\n\r\nNOTE: Should Memorial Day, July 4, Labor Day, Thanksgiving, Christmas or New Year’s Day fall in a given week, collections following the holiday are moved back one day.\r\n\r\nYARD WASTE pick up will start the first Tuesday of March.\r\n\r\nYARD WASTE pick up ends the last Tuesday of December.\r\n\r\nCHRISTMAS TREE removal will take place on the second Tuesday in January.', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '155', '', '', '2012-06-29 12:46:11', '2012-06-29 12:46:11', '', 0, 'http://www.stregispark.net/?p=155', 11, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(156, 1, '2011-10-14 12:11:39', '2011-10-14 12:11:39', 'The City of St. Regis Park has a Mayor/Council form of government. The Mayor is elected by popular vote and serves a term of four (4) years. There are seven (7) council members, who are elected by popular vote and serve a term of two (2) years.\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n\r\n<tr valign="top" style="background:#E8E8E8;">\r\n<td width="20%"><strong>Brandt Davis</strong><br />297-2820<br /><br /><a href="mailto:cityofstregispark@mcmahanfire.com">cityofstregispark@mcmahanfire.com</a></td>\r\n<td width="80%"><a href="http://www.stregispark.net/?attachment_id=127"><img src="http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/davis-100x100.jpg" alt="Brandt Davis" title="davis" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-127" /></a><strong>Mayor</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td><strong>Bob Ecker</strong><br />458-3037<br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.stregispark.net/?attachment_id=128"><img src="http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/ecker-100x100.jpg" alt="Bob Ecker" title="ecker" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-128" /></a><strong>Building Permits</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top" style="background:#E8E8E8;">\r\n<td><strong>Bill Hodapp</strong><br />671-9469<br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.stregispark.net/?attachment_id=129"><img src="http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/hodapp-100x100.jpg" alt="Bill Hodapp" title="hodapp" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-129" /></a><strong>Public Safety</strong><br />Mr. Hodapp resides on Sir Johns Court with his wife (Sue) and 2 children (Ben and Katie).  He has been a resident of St. Regis Park over 10 years.  Mr. Hodapp was appointed a Councilman in September 2011 and is responsible for public safety in the neighborhood.  He is graduate of Eastern Kentucky University in 1988 with a BS in Fire and Safety Engineering and works for RMR Recycling as the Environmental Health and Safety Manager.<br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td><strong>Sandy Macy</strong><br />938-2441<br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td><strong>Sanitation, Snow Removal and Yard Sales</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top" style="background:#E8E8E8;">\r\n<td><strong>Laurel Rowland</strong><br />456-5545<br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td><strong>Communications Facilitator</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td><strong>James Walsh</strong><br />452-6515<br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.stregispark.net/?attachment_id=130"><img src="http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/walsh-100x100.jpg" alt="James Walsh" title="walsh" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-130" /></a><strong>Finance</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top" style="background:#E8E8E8;">\r\n<td><strong>Bernard Watts</strong><br />459-0995<br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td><strong>Parking and Yard Sales</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td><strong>Cheryl Willet</strong><br />458-8386<br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td><strong>Special Events</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr><td colspan="2">&nbsp;</td></tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2"><strong>The City also has three appointed officers:</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr><td colspan="2">&nbsp;</td></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top" style="background:#E8E8E8;">\r\n<td><strong>Talbott Allen</strong><br />451-3776<br /><br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td><strong>City Clerk/Treasurer</strong><br />Mr. Allen previously served two terms as mayor of St. Regis Park and two stints as City Clerk/Treasurer.  He also serves on the Board of Trustees McMahan Fire Protection District as Secretary/Treasurer, the Ronald McDonald House Charities of Kentuckiana Board of Directors and is the Chairman of the Komen Louisville Race for the Cure.<br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td><strong>Bob Graves</strong><br />451-2047<br /><br /><a href="ashtin@netzero.net">ashtin@netzero.net</a></td>\r\n<td><strong>Assistant City Clerk/Assistant Treasurer</strong><br />Mr. Graves resides on Stormon Court and has been a resident since 1976.  He is a Vietnam combat veteran, retired Army National Guard Lieutenant Colonel and retired business owner.  He was appointed Assistant City Clerk/Assistant Treasurer in October 2011.<br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top" style="background:#E8E8E8;">\r\n<td><strong>Andrew Amon</strong><br />451-6360<br />&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.stregispark.net/?attachment_id=126"><img src="http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/amon-100x100.jpg" alt="Andrew Amon" title="amon" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-126" /></a><strong>Citation Officer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nBeginning with the new terms of office in January 2007 the Mayor is paid $500.00 per month and Council members are paid $100.00 per month.\r\n\r\nThe positions of mayor and city council are obtained by filing for non-partisan elections held the first Tuesday of November. To run for Mayor or a council position a person must file with the Board of Elections prior to August 12 in order to be placed on the ballot in November. For more information contact the Board of Elections at 574-6100.\r\n\r\nThe City Council meets on the 1st Tuesday of every month at 7:30 p.m.. The meetings are held at the McMahan Fire District, 4318 Taylorsville Road. Notices of the meetings are published in the monthly newsletter. The meetings are open to the public and your comments are welcome during Citizen Participation at the beginning of every City Council meeting.', 'Council', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '10-revision-64', '', '', '2011-10-14 12:11:39', '2011-10-14 12:11:39', '', 10, 'http://www.stregispark.net/index.php/2011/10/14/10-revision-64/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
