r style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #e8e8e8;" valign="top">\r\n<td><strong>Talbott Allen</strong>\r\n451-3776\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td><strong>City Clerk/Treasurer</strong>\r\nMr. Allen previously served two terms as mayor of St. Regis Park and two stints as City Clerk/Treasurer. He also serves on the Board of Trustees McMahan Fire Protection District as Secretary/Treasurer, the Ronald McDonald House Charities of Kentuckiana Board of Directors and is the Chairman of the Komen Louisville Race for the Cure.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td><strong>Bob Graves</strong>\r\n451-2047\r\n\r\n<a href="ashtin@netzero.net">ashtin@netzero.net</a></td>\r\n<td><strong>Assistant City Clerk/Assistant Treasurer</strong>\r\nMr. Graves resides on Stormon Court and has been a resident since 1976. He is a Vietnam combat veteran, retired Army National Guard Lieutenant Colonel and retired business owner. He was appointed Assistant City Clerk/Assistant Treasurer in October 2011.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #e8e8e8;" valign="top">\r\n<td><strong>Andrew Amon</strong>\r\n451-6360</td>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.stregispark.net/?attachment_id=126"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-126" title="amon" src="http://www.stregispark.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/amon-100x100.jpg" alt="Andrew Amon" width="100" height="100" /></a><strong>Citation Officer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nBeginning with the new terms of office in January 2007 the Mayor is paid $500.00 per month and Council members are paid $100.00 per month.\r\n\r\nThe positions of mayor and city council are obtained by filing for non-partisan elections held the first Tuesday of November. To run for Mayor or a council position a person must file with the Board of Elections prior to August 12 in order to be placed on the ballot in November. For more information contact the Board of Elections at 574-6100.\r\n\r\nThe City Council meets on the 1st Tuesday of every month at 7:30 p.m.. The meetings are held at the McMahan Fire District, 4318 Taylorsville Road. Notices of the meetings are published in the monthly newsletter. The meetings are open to the public and your comments are welcome during Citizen Participation at the beginning of every City Council meeting.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Council', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '10-revision-79', '', '', '2012-05-01 21:34:01', '2012-05-01 21:34:01', '', 10, 'http://www.stregispark.net/10-revision-79/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
